  "text": "In the future, better treatment outcomes for patients with a poor prognosis (IDH wild-type, absence of 1p19 co-deletion, high CHI3L1 expression and low NTRK2 expression) might be proposed by combining conventional chemotherapy (radiotherapy and temozolomide) with CHI3L1-targeted inhibitors, especially in grade IV [CITATION_1] . In grade II patients with a very good prognosis, therapeutic de-escalation or treatment with NTRK2 inhibitor may be considered.",
